<item>
            <title>[LU-13090] fix lfs_migrate -p for file with an existing pool</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13090</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It appears that &quot;&lt;tt&gt;-A -p &amp;lt;name&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; does not behave as expected...  The -p is ignored. It would be good if -p works correctly, so that files can be migrated to a specific pool.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# lfs_migrate --dry-run -v -A -p HDD foo 
stripe_count=1,stripe_size=262144,pool=SSD
dry run, skipped
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
